item.title: comma club writeup
item.description: Challenge description link to challange “We need somone to run our vote tallying machine, and it needs to be someone trustworthy. Apparently there’s some problem if a candidate gets too many votes. Shouldn’t be a problem for us in Wyoming though.” nc comma-club.chal.hackthe.vote 1337 file Solution After inspecting the checksec output, we can see that the binary is not stripped and has all the protections disabled. We can also see that the binary is a 64-bit ELF file.
